Entry Level Numerical Control Programmer - Machined Parts

Boeing

- Portland, OR 97204

At Boeing, we are all innovators on a mission to connect, protect, explore and inspire. From the seabed to outer space, youll learn and grow, contributing to work that shapes the world. Find your future with us.

At Boeing Portland we engage the talent, pride and passion of people to be the leading supplier of flight critical, complex machined hardware to all of Boeing Commercial Airplanes for today and tomorrow. Here at Boeing Portland, we celebrate a culture around the One Boeing Production Systemour unique way of transforming our lean Production System to align the sites culture on safety, quality and continuous improvement. This culture engages our employees because their thoughts, ideas, and talents are valued. We are looking for teammates to join us that will be fully engaged and adaptable, will be team players and problem solvers, and will be excellent communicators.

Boeing Commercial Airplanes is seeking Entry Level Numerical Control (NC) Programmers to support our Fabrication Organization in Portland, OR.

Position Responsibilities:
Develops, revises and verifies Machine Control Data (MCD) and geometry.
Provides machine operator instructions and documentation for automated or numerically controlled equipment per established process.
This position may support the Tool Data Management (TDM) implementation team before transitioning into NC Programming.

The position must meet Export Control compliance requirements, therefore a US Person as defined by 22 C.F.R. ยง 120.15 is required. US Person includes US Citizen, lawful permanent resident, refugee, or asylee.

Basic Qualifications (Required Skills / Experience):
Experience with CAD/CAM (computer aided design/computer aided manufacturing) systems and tools
Experience reading, understanding, and interpreting engineering drawings and specifications
Experience with manufacturing methods and processes
Preferred Qualifications:
Experience working in a machine shop or manufacturing environment is preferred.
Ability to select the best method of producing parts, tools or assemblies
Typical Education / Experience:

Typically acquired through advanced education (e.g. Associate) or an equivalent combination of education and experience (e.g. 2 years' related work experience).

This position is located in Portland, OR and does not offer relocation. Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense.

This is a union represented position.

Boeing is a Drug Free Workplace where post offer applicants and employees are subject to testing for marijuana, cocaine, opioids, amphetamines, PCP, and alcohol when criteria is met as outlined in our policies.

